\subsection{Method \code{add_order()}}{
Place an OCO Order

Places a new OCO (One-Cancels-Other) order on KuCoin Spot. An OCO order
combines a limit order with a stop-limit order. When one side triggers or
fills, the other side is automatically cancelled.
\subsection{Workflow}{
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Validation}: Verifies \code{symbol} format and matches \code{side} against allowed values.
\item \strong{Body Construction}: Builds the request body with price, size, stop, and limit parameters.
\item \strong{Request}: Authenticated POST to the OCO order endpoint.
\item \strong{Parsing}: Returns \code{data.table} with the assigned \code{order_id}.
}
}

\subsection{API Endpoint}{

\verb{POST https://api.kucoin.com/api/v3/oco/order}
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\href{https://www.kucoin.com/docs-new/rest/spot-trading/orders/add-oco-order}{KuCoin Add OCO Order}

Verified: 2026-05-23
}

\subsection{Automated Trading Usage}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Take-Profit + Stop-Loss}: Place a sell OCO with \code{price} as take-profit and \code{stopPrice}/\code{limitPrice} as
stop-loss to protect positions automatically.
\item \strong{Bracket Entry}: Use a buy OCO to enter a position at a limit price while also setting a stop-entry above
resistance.
\item \strong{Client OID Tracking}: Set \code{clientOid} to a unique strategy identifier for programmatic order tracking and
reconciliation.
}
}

