\subsection{Method \code{cancel_all()}}{
Cancel All OCO Orders

Cancels all active OCO orders matching the given filters. Can filter by
\code{symbol} or specify individual \code{orderIds}. If no filters are provided,
all active OCO orders are cancelled.
\subsection{Workflow}{
\enumerate{
\item \strong{Filter Construction}: Builds query parameters from the provided filter list.
\item \strong{Request}: Authenticated DELETE to the batch cancellation endpoint.
\item \strong{Cancellation}: KuCoin cancels all matching OCO orders.
\item \strong{Parsing}: Returns \code{data.table} with cancelled order IDs.
}
}

\subsection{API Endpoint}{

\verb{DELETE https://api.kucoin.com/api/v3/oco/orders}
}

\subsection{Official Documentation}{

\href{https://www.kucoin.com/docs-new/rest/spot-trading/orders/batch-cancel-oco-order}{KuCoin Batch Cancel OCO Orders}

Verified: 2026-05-23
}

\subsection{Automated Trading Usage}{
\itemize{
\item \strong{Emergency Kill Switch}: Call with no filters to cancel all OCO orders during market anomalies or system
errors.
\item \strong{Symbol Cleanup}: Pass \code{symbol} to cancel all OCO orders for a specific pair when exiting a position
entirely.
\item \strong{Selective Batch Cancel}: Pass specific \code{orderIds} to cancel a subset of OCO orders during strategy
rebalancing.
}
}

